{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"META EVIDENCE from the single-pass G3/G4 review of THIS epic (run as the merge+pack extreme — one subagent over all 6 children instead of the 2N fan-out): evaluating all children TOGETHER IMPROVED cross-child (G4) recall — it surfaced an inter-child gap (S2's unverified prompt relocation) that a one-child-at-a-time fan-out would have MISSED (each child reads fine alone; the gap lives between S2 and S6). This validates the design hypothesis that G3/G4 (cross-child criteria) benefit from seeing children together. CAVEAT: attention skewed to the first/most-annotated children; TAIL children got less granular review (recency/salience bias). => batching preserves/improves cross-child fidelity but risks per-child DEPTH on tail children; the REQUIRED structured per-child output guardrail (already in S5) is ESSENTIAL and must also apply to S4. S6's eval should specifically check TAIL-child recall."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782572466917749001,"uuid":"4f7bc80a-e0fc-420e-9aee-99b6cf18d69d"}